## 💼 LinkedIn Post (Ready to Copy-Paste)

**Headline:** Stop Googling. Start Agenting. 🤖📚

Researching technical topics and academic papers is a massive time sink. As an AI Engineer based in South Korea, I’ve seen how often "AI fluff" ruins technical content.

That’s why I built and open-sourced **Agentic Author** — an autonomous multi-agent research engine that works like a high-end editorial team on your local machine.

**Why is this different?**
Unlike standard LLM prompts, this system uses a stateful graph (LangGraph) to orchestrate specialized agents:
🔍 **Strategist:** Plans the deep-dive.
📚 **Researcher:** Scours Arxiv and the web for evidence.
🧪 **Distiller:** Compresses raw data into a technical fact sheet.
✍️ **Writer:** Drafts with precision (no fluff allowed!).
⚖️ **Critic:** A reflection loop that rejects any draft that isn't up to academic standards.

**Key Technical Specs:**
✅ **Orchestration:** LangGraph (Python)
✅ **Brain:** Gemini 1.5 Flash (via BYOK - Bring Your Own Key)
✅ **Memory:** Local ChromaDB (The system gets smarter with every blog it writes!)
✅ **Cost:** Optimized for the FREE tier.

I wanted to make this accessible for researchers, developers, and students. No complex cloud setup—just clone, add your keys, and run it locally.

